 062:         """
 063:         For every item the cosine similarity against other items depends on whether they have users in common. 
 064:         The more common users the higher the similarity.
 065:         
 066:         The basic implementation is:
 067:         - Select the first item
 068:         - Loop through all other items
 069:         -- Given the two items, get the users they have in common
 070:         -- Update the similarity considering all common users
 071:         
 072:         That is VERY slow due to the common user part, in which a long data structure is looped multiple times.
 073:         
 074:         A better way is to use the data structure in a different way skipping the search part, getting directly
 075:         the information we need.
 076:         
 077:         The implementation here used is:
 078:         - Select the first item
 079:         - Initialize a zero valued array for the similarities
 080:         - Get the users who rated the first item
 081:         - Loop through the users
 082:         -- Given a user, get the items he rated (second item)
 083:         -- Update the similarity of the items he rated
 084:         
 085:         
 086:         """
